Policy.acknowledgement_statement: The Offspring Sex Impacts DNA Methylation and Gene Expression in Placentae from Women with Diabetes During Pregnancy study is a subset of data from the Prenatal Conditions and the Pathway to Obesity and Diabetes in Children study supported by the National Institute of Diabetes and Digestive and Kidney Diseases (NIDDK). The data reported here were supplied by Steven D. Chernausek, MD (Principal Investigator), the University of Oklahoma Health Sciences Center, the Children’s Hospital of Philadelphia, the Chickasaw Nation, and Choctaw Nation of Oklahoma. This manuscript was not prepared in collaboration with Investigators of the Offspring Sex Impacts DNA Methylation and Gene Expression in Placentae from Women with Diabetes During Pregnancy study, the Chickasaw Nation or the Choctaw Nation of Oklahoma and does not necessarily reflect the opinions or views of the investigators, the institutions listed above or the NIDDK.
